name: Eduardo Garcia Posadas
sales_notes__c:
Intial discovery email notes:
How did you hear about us?
In a Dremio video

 

Are you seeking a demo for an internal or external use case? If external, please provide the company name you are supporting so we can link you to the appropriate Account Executive on our end.
For an Internal case in Cariad

 

What is the current system of data access management?
An internal tool base on keycloak, but we need an extra layer of management for a new data platform that we are creating

 

What are you hoping to accomplish with XXXX? I saw that you mentioned centralized access management and policy management. Is it possible to get some further color for the project at hand?
We are creating a new data platform for Cariad. Since there are duplicated data products and too many silos, we want to provide a platform that offers portable services/tools for our engineers to develop multiple use cases, that platform will cover the following areas:

Ingestion: ingest data from our multiple platforms of the cars and use cases
Pre-Processing: offer a service to handle real-time and batch data with a multi-engine approach
Storage: offer real-time and batch services using technologies like Lakehouse, Kafka, Cassandra, and Search Engine
Delivery: Deliver the data for multiple uses cases in notebooks, dashboards, and semantic layer
 

The platform will cover multiple data teams and we need a tool to centralize the management of access, policies, and governance. This will allow us to centralize the management for all the products that we want to offer to our data teams.

 

Do you work with any of the following: AWS, Azure, GCP, Databricks, or Snowflake (If none please note what you work with within your architecture)?
AWS and Azure, we are evaluating databricks or Dremio as a lakehouse.

 

Do you have an implementation timeline for this project?
We are in the initial phase, creating an MVP in the 1st quarter of 2023.

 

We recently met with another member of the Volkswagen Co. so we were curious about your procurement process and if you were in touch with that individual (the contact's name was Christoph Spohr)
Cariad being a company from Volkswagen rely in processes similar to them. I am not in contact with Christoph but could be good to know if somehow his product is related to our product or even Cariad.

By the way, if Volkswagen already have you as a vendor for sure the process will be easier.


Lee Kickced off call by qualifying if we could sell to Cariad. 

Technology: found us from a dremio video. he is looking to build a lakehouse. has relationships with AWS and Microsoft. Some teams are moving AWS to AZURE. some clouds still use AWS. Uses Openshift and maybe Azure. 


Why now: in technology team CTO has decreed they need a de-siloing platform to be used by all players that are working on creating autonomous cars. 
Eduardo stated the other option was another vendor for data managment. perhaps also self build platform. 

Timeline: starting project now. POC first quarter. Purchase Q2. GO Live Q3

Next Steps: Looking for more info/demo on how to enable with Dremio and/or Starburst. Sometime in next 2 weeks. He also wants to show this to 4 of his architect colleagues. Presents this to the platform owner (economic buyer). Willl get NDA executed. Eduardo will make intro to the procurement team.

name: Manoj Bansal
sales_notes__c:
-How did you hear about us? 

Google search and word of mouth

 

-Are you seeking a demo for an internal or external use case? If external, please provide the company name you are supporting so we can link you to the appropriate Account Executive on our end. : 

I represent BlackRock which is the largest Asset Management Firm in the world. We are looking at XXXX to be able to govern fine grained data access for our internal use cases as well as if possible for our external end customers. Our need is also to extend the control on the data usage restrictions as per licensed contracts.

 

-What is the current system of data access management? 

The current system of access management is through inhouse API based solution built which provides token based entitlement access.

 

-What are you hoping to accomplish with XXXX? I saw your notes on your demo request form. Is it possible to provide additional clarity?

Blackrock is a consumer and data distributor as well to its clients for multiple data domain (ESG, Reference data etc.) which it receives from various 3rd party vendors like MSCI, Reuters etc. BlackRock also generates its own data and there are Client specific data also shared with BlackRock. We have licensing agreement on the data subscription and its usage and also have to abide by the same when we are distributing this data to our end clients as per their subscriptions and usage entitlement. Through XXXX we would like to be able to control and govern access and usage of the data in a fine grained manner as per subscriptions through a single point of enforcement. Our data sits in Sybase, Sybase IQ on premise and Snowflake on Azure cloud.  

 

-I notitced you mentioned using Snowflakes and Sybase. Do you work with any of the following: AWS, Azure, GCP, Databricks? 

BLK use Azure cloud for Snowflake but Sybase & Sybase IQ is hosted on premise. We are also looking for on prem solution for data security

 

-Do you have an implementation timeline for this project?

Couple of months for making a firm decision.
